article.headline: Iowa St. 61, UC Davis 58
article.story: AMES, Iowa -- Diante Garrett banked in a short jumper with 11.7 seconds left to give Iowa State the lead and the Cyclones escaped with a 61-58 victory over UC Davis in a season opener Friday night. Iowa State rallied from 14 points down midway through the second half to survive in the first round of the World Vision Classic. Jamie Vanderbeken rebounded a UC Davis miss after Garrett's basket and made two free throws with 3.6 seconds remaining to wrap it up. Vanderbeken, a junior college transfer, led Iowa State with 14 points and 10 rebounds. Craig Brackins, limited to just 2 minutes in the first half because of two quick fouls, added 12 points for the Cyclones. Notre Dame transfer Joe Harden led UC Davis with 19 points and Vince Oliver scored 16.
